The Gd(III), Dy(III) and Sm(III) complexes of Schiff base derived from acetoacetanilide and 1,3-diaminopropane, [MX3(LH2)], where X = Cl−, NO3
−, NCS−, have been synthesized in alcohol and characterized by elemental analysis, electrical conductance in non-aqueous solvents, spectral as well as magnetic susceptibility measurements. In these complexes, ligand LH2 acts as a tetradentate ligand coordinating through the two azomethine nitrogen atoms and the two enolizable carbonyl group of acetoacetanilide moiety. The antifungal activity of the ligands LH2 and some of their complexes were evaluated by agar diffusion method against the fungi Candida albicans and Fusarium oxysporum using Fluconazole as standard (Santhi and Radhakrishnan Namboori, 2013) (Fig. 5
).
